B24 - Design and implement access control of your choice

Objective
The goal of this activity was to design and implement an access control mechanism to restrict and manage user permission.

Method
I used a document-sharing platform to implement access control by restricting permissions for another user. The aim was to control access to the document and prevent unauthorised modifications.

Implementation
A Word document was created and shared with another user with view-only access. This ensured that the user could read the content but could not make any changes to the document.

Evaluation
Strengths:
- prevents unauthorised editing or modification of the document
- maintains data integrity by restricting write accesss
- simple and effective access control mechanism
Limitations:
- does not prevent screenshots or sopying of content
- requires correct configuration of sharing settings

Outcome
The implementation successfully restricted access to the document, ensuring tha tonly auhtorised viewing was allowed while preventing editing.

Reflection
This activity demonstrated how access control can be effectively implemented even in simple systems. It reinforced the importance of controlling user permissions to protect data from unauthorised changes.
